God never ceases to amaze me! Sky is the limit….🙌🏾

Story time: Have you every heard the story of the ugly duckling. Yeah, that’s me! If I told you that ppl closest to me told me that modeling was a waste of my time. Would you believe me? Super grateful for those who continue to see more in me than I’ve been able to see in myself. 🥹 Thank you for talking me out of my overthinking. Thank you continuing to push me to believe bigger. Thank you encouraging me when I’ve felt discouraged. I am sorry that I haven’t done more sooner but God is faithful + I owe me + the world more. 

For anyone who is experiencing any self doubt:

1. You are amazing
2. You have everything you need
3. Start where you are
4. Believe in yourself
5. Don’t ever give up

Special thank you to @lululemon for the opportunity. Thank you to @jabariabasi + @jamesro__ for you all’s help along the way🔌. Thank you @marvn._  @critaquinn @airkenya @samwith2ms for all the work that you do! 

@debraowens4186 this is only the beginning. Thank you for everything 🤞🏾🙏🏾. 

@laspoon + @eboneejmua  I appreciate you for coming through to show love. 🫶🏾

Week in review: 

1. Wrapped up the week with Christmas + Cookies 👧🏽🥰

2. Week 6 of an amazing Nonprofit Leadership Cohort. 

3. One of my favorite breakfast meals. A Grit bowl! (Why mustard? - Mustard contains antioxidants that are anti-cancer, antibacterial, antiviral, antifungal, anti-inflammatory and help fight disease)

If raising a child was a video….

1. Learn and grow with them. 

2. Have an ear + eye for the things that they want. (I got her a scooter b/c after our first trip to LA, we rode them and she loves them)

3. Encourage them to challenge themselves + try new things. 

4. Allow them to make mistakes yet make them feel loved and supported without discouraging their spirit. 

5. Be ready to catch them should they lose their balance along the way.

Day 7.

With 2022 coming to an end, my spirit began to fill with feelings of anxiety, lack, and doubt. The thoughts of not being where I want to be, the perceived L’s I’ve taken, and the seeds of defeat tried to take root. 

I often turn to writing as it quiets my mind and helps me process my thoughts. So as I wrote some time in December, The Lord began to speak to me and He shared with me this prayer that I’d like to share and pray over you. 

Honestly, recorded this a week ago and almost let the selfish desire for perfection keep me from posting but while lying on the couch tears streamed from eyes, God told me to get up and share His word.

We did a ting yesterday 😬🐍

This is the first time I’ve ever even touched a snake so I figured go big or go home, right?! 😆 

📕 Super Quick Story | Words of Encouragement 💫 

TWO THINGS

1. We all have “fears” but what you focus on becomes your frequency. By no means am I saying, holding snakes is the answer in the event you’re fearful like snakes but what I am saying is LET GO OF FEAR. 

2. I thought my heart might have been racing but I was super calm. I think in my mind, I felt that if I was calm then the snake would be calm. If I acted fearful then the snake would acknowledge that energy and act accordingly. Saying all that to say, we are all energy and I was aware of my frequency. I tuned in to  being calm, meek, respectful, and loving.

Happy Father’s Day! 👑

📚 Story time:

You’ve changed me in ways I could’ve never imagined. I’ll be honest, I never saw my life with you but since you were born, I can’t imagine life without you. I’m honored that God chose me to be your dad. 

My daughter’s initials are TKO and when I tell you she knocked me out but I woke up a new version of myself not without faults but with a renewed faith that God’s plan is always better. I woke up with unconditional love in my heart that I’ve never experienced before. Because if you, I’m a different fighter now + know I’ll always be in your corner. 

I’ll say this last thing…I do not have a close relationship with my father at all but I know one thing that’s for damn sure….my daughter will never be able to say that about me. I stand on that with all my existence.

Day 6: Two Tips To Help You Supercharge Your Week 💪🏾

1. Proper Rest -  Your brains need time to rest and recharge in order to be productive. When we don’t get enough sleep, we’re more likely to have difficulty concentrating, and be less creative. 

2. Proper Nutrition- Like an expensive car, your brain functions best when it gets only premium fuel. Eating high-quality foods that contain lots of vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants nourishes the brain and protects it from oxidative stress.

Let’s just say I haven’t take class in some time. I’ve been rehabbing through a knee injury for the past few months. I had a slight tear in my meniscus and aggravated it. Constant swelling, stiffness, soreness, etc. Simply walking almost took me out at times lol.

Day 15: Taco Tuesday 🌮 

I want to share 3 things about the importance of cooking with your child  or partner + 2 things I do to make my tacos slap! 👋🏾 

1. Allows you all to spend quality time together and talk!
(You might be amazed at what they have to say)

2. They learn how to cook! 
(I mean not so much for others but themselves…sheesh. Self sufficiency can take you long way)

3. Allowing them help create a sense of inclusion and corroborating. 

(Anybody go up with: Hey, what’s for dinner?…whatever I cook and you better eat it or you can go to bed hungry! 🥴 or You’re not leaving this table until that plate is clean! 🫠)

4. Season your meat prior to adding taco seasoning. 

5. Cook your meat with diced red, yellow, orange peppers, and onions.

Day 16:  Don’t overthink it. 

I must admit, overthinking has been a growth opportunity for me. There have been many times where I’ll will think myself to sleep or to a place of inaction. 

I will say this, often overthinking creates problems that don’t exist and can cause you to worry about things that aren’t likely to happen. You’re brain processes 60,000 - 80,000 thoughts a day and 95% of your thoughts are repetitive. The mind is a power thing and it’s important to be mindful of how your thoughts impact the world around you. 

Your mind is a muscle and requires training, rest, and proper nutrition just as your physical body does in order to perform at it’s best. 

Be kind to yourself and give yourself grace.

Day 17: Body Dysmorphia is real but doesn’t have to be your reality. 

You Look Amazing…Yes, I’m Talking To You 🫵🏾 

A form of BDD is Muscle Dysmorphia which is belief that one’s body is “too small” or “not muscular enough” despite having a normal build, or in many cases, an objectively extremely “buff” physique. Bullying or teasing early in life can be reasons for this and leading to low self-esteem. (Also me)

Thank you to my brothers who always big me up and make me get uncomfortable. Working out with you all was the FIRST time I’ve EVER worked out in public without a shirt. You all’s encouragement to be unapologetically yourself + love the skin has been eye opening. Crazy to think that I’ve been in way better shape and way stronger yet was so full of insecurities…even still. 

Prime example is that this video was recorded in Feb 2023 + because I didn’t feel like I was “in shape”….I never posted it. 

I’m still a work in progress but in life and fitness journey seek progress over perfection. 

Love y’all 🙏🏾
Day 18: Whatever makes you smile, do that!

Day 19: My Steve Urkel Story 🤓

When I tell you I used to PRAY until my knees were ashy that one day I’d turn from Steve Urkel to Stefan Urquelle 😮‍💨

You couldn’t tell me that Steve and I weren’t twins. I swear my life was his life except I wasn’t clumsy. I was hyper athletic but the sports goggles turned that persona all the way back down. 

You name it, it had it…acne, boils, buck teeth, braces, “homemade” haircuts, thrift clothes, big feet, skinny, bullies, heartbreak, and more. Lol

I will tell you there are some things that haven’t changed….

1. Prayer and seeking God
2. Believing that better is always on the way
3. The love of learning 
4. Understanding the value of people who truly love you where you are
5. Choosing to smile even when it hurts

I’ve always wanted to take over + turn up a school, after school program, youth center, etc. With the support of sponsors, some amazing volunteers, coupled with incredible leadership and a loving staff…we did it!

CALLING ALL DOPE DADS IN ATLANTA - On Sunday Sept 24th at 10am sharp, were excited to announce @teamdopedads is joining forces with @thedadgang + @walmart to bring the March of Dads tour to ATL. 

The March of Dads campaign is a groundbreaking public demonstration that was started in 2018 to unite active dads across the nation around changing that narrative of black fatherhood. 

Together we’re creating a spaces for dads to meet, bond and build with their local tribes in every city. 

So far, dads in NY, LA, and DC have showed up and showed out. 

ATLANTA IT'S OUR TURN to join the march and be a part of history in the making! We’re not leaving any dope dads behind. It may not be father’s day but this the dad link up that we’ve all been waiting for.
